      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 12-year-old boy is brought to a pediatric outpatient department in an urban hospital in India with his parents, who are concerned about his recent onset of hand tremors and occasional jerking movements. The boy, previously healthy and an active cricket player, has noticed these symptoms worsening over the past month, affecting his ability to play. An ophthalmological examination reveals Kayser-Fleischer (KF) rings, and an MRI indicates bilateral hypodense lesions in the basal ganglia. Laboratory tests show elevated liver enzymes (AST and ALT), and a liver biopsy reveals increased copper levels. Based on these findings, a diagnosis of Wilson&#39;s disease is made. Which of the following statements about Wilson&#39;s disease is NOT true?</span></span></span></p>",
